    "content": "# The Reward Points Game: How to Earn Money with Credit Cards\n\n## Easy Finance Newsletter | Issue #5 Mar 2026\n\nCredit cards are often viewed as debt traps. However, if used with discipline, a credit card can actually make you money rather than cost you money.\n\nBy understanding how credit card billing cycles, cashbacks, and reward points work, you can earn thousands of rupees every year on your regular household expenses.\n\n─────────────────────────\n💳 1. Choose Cashback Cards for Daily Spends\n\nIf you do not travel frequently, cashback credit cards are the best choice. \n\nCo-branded cards offer flat cashbacks (often 1% to 5%) on utility bills, grocery shopping, online deliveries, and fuel. \n\nIf your monthly household expenses are ₹30,000, a average 3% cashback earns you **₹900 per month (₹10,800 per year)** back in your pocket for expenses you had to pay anyway.\n\n─────────────────────────\n📅 2. Leverage the Interest-Free Period\n\nCredit cards offer an interest-free period of up to 45 to 50 days. \n\nInstead of spending debit cash immediately, keep your monthly budget in a high-interest savings account or sweep-in FD. Pay your expenses using a credit card.\n\nAt the end of the cycle, pay the credit card bill in full using the funds in your savings account. You earn interest on your money while using the bank's money interest-free.\n\n─────────────────────────\n✈️ 3. Maximize Travel Reward Points\n\nFor frequent travelers, air miles and hotel reward points offer huge value. \n\nBy accumulating points on airline co-branded cards, you can redeem them for free flights, seat upgrades, and luxury hotel stays. Many cards also offer free domestic and international airport lounge access, saving you airport food costs.\n\n─────────────────────────\n⚠️ The Golden Rule: Pay in Full\n\nThe reward game only works if you **pay your total outstanding balance in full every single month**. \n\nIf you pay only the \"minimum amount due,\" the bank charges interest rates of 36% to 42% per annum, which instantly wipes out all rewards and cashbacks.\n\n─────────────────────────\n📋 Key Takeaways\n• Co-branded credit cards offer cashbacks up to 5% on regular spending.\n• Leverage interest-free periods to keep your cash earning interest.\n• Never pay interest; pay the total outstanding bill in full every month.\n\n─────────────────────────\n🎯 Action Step\nReview your bank statements from the last three months. Identify your largest spending categories (e.g. online shopping, groceries, travel) and research which credit card offers the highest cashback or reward points for those specific categories."
